description: In a statement late on Tuesday night, Oman announced it had conducted “recent discussions and contacts” with the United States and “relevant authorities” in the Ansarallah-controlled Yemen.
title: Oman says it mediated US-Yemen ‘ceasefire’

description: India said early Wednesday that it had conducted strikes on what it called “terrorist infrastructure” in Pakistan, two weeks after an attack by armed militants killed more than two dozen civilians in Indian-administered Kashmir, the New York Times reported.
title: India strikes three sites inside Pakistan

description: TEHRAN - The "For Palestine" group, a collective of Iranian workers, academics, artists, and intellectuals, has released a second statement denouncing Israel and the complicit global order for the regime's crimes in the besieged Gaza Strip.
title: Iranian group "For Palestine" issues second statement on Israeli genocide in Gaza

description: TEHRAN - In a note, Shargh addressed Paris's destructive approach in the Iran nuclear talks.
title: France's duplicity

description: MADRID – During his visit to Pakistan, Iranian Foreign Minister Seyed Abbas Araghchi held a telephone conversation on Monday with Kaja Kallas, High Representative of the European Union for Foreign Affairs and Security Policy.
title: Iran opens the door to dialogue: New opportunities for the EU on the world stage

description: TEHRAN – Iranian Foreign Ministry Abbas Araghchi has sharply criticized the destructive role of Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu in exacerbating regional instability and undermining diplomatic efforts between Iran and the United States.
title: Netanyahu meddling in U.S. government to drag it into another disaster: Iran FM

description: TEHRAN – Iranian Foreign Ministry Abbas Araghchi has sharply criticized the destructive role of Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu in exacerbating regional instability and undermining diplomatic efforts between Iran and the United States.
title: Netanyahu seeking to drag it into another disaster: Iran

description: TEHRAN – The Iranian government spokesperson has cautioned against excessive optimism in ongoing indirect negotiations with Washington.
title: ‘U.S. dishonesty proven repeatedly’, Iran says is committed but realistic toward talks

description: TEHRAN—Mohammad Eslami, Head of the Atomic Energy Organization of Iran (AEOI), emphasized the pivotal role of uranium enrichment in the nation’s technological and industrial sovereignty, underscoring the country’s commitment to advance its civilian nuclear program under a newly finalized 20-year strategic plan.
title: Enrichment ‘core’ to Iran’s industrial power, declares nuclear chief amid strategic blueprint launch

description: TEHRAN – Iran’s Deputy Foreign Minister Saeed Khatibzadeh has reaffirmed the strategic importance of the Republic of Azerbaijan for Iran, highlighting the growing momentum in bilateral relations and the two countries’ shared cultural and regional interests.
title: Tehran-Baku relations enter promising new phase: Iran deputy FM

description: TEHRAN – Recent statements by Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu and U.S. Secretary of Defense Pete Hegseth, who have threatened unwarranted action against Tehran based on unsubstantiated claims of involvement in Yemeni resistance against Israeli aggression, have drawn a firm response from Iran, with the country’s Ambassador to the United Nations promising a “swift” response to any illegal aggression by Washington or Tel Aviv.
title: Iran says ‘swift’ response will follow any US-Israeli aggression

description: TEHRAN -  The Iranian Foreign Ministry spokesperson announced on Tuesday night that the date for the next round of indirect talks between Iran and the United States is being studied.
title: The date for next round of Iran-US talks under study: Foreign Ministry

description: In a meeting that got pretty tense towards the end, Donald Trump dug in his heels on his tariff policy, insisting there was nothing Canadian PM Mark Carney could say to make him change his mind and lift tariffs imposed on Canada. Trump insisted the U.S. doesn’t want cars and steel from Canada “because we’re making our own”.
title: Key takeaways from Trump-Carney meeting

description: TEHRAN – A deadly Israeli-American aerial assault on Yemen and its airport has prompted stern warnings of escalation from the Sanaa government.
title: Yemen warns Israelis of “severe consequences”

description: BEIRUT — To serve its project of dismantling the fabric of West Asia’s minorities and to accelerate its Israelization project, Israel has been exploiting the Druze since October 7, 2023, by enticing them to abandon their Syrian identity and join the so-called “State of Israel”.
title: HTS extremism gives chance to Israel to lure Syrian Druze

description: TEHRAN - The official approval of a plan for the complete occupation of the Gaza Strip by the cabinet of the Zionist regime has sparked a wave of protest and concern among the families of the hostages.
title: Start of internal rupture: Israel on brink of social collapse

description: TEHRAN - President Donald Trump and Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu are walking down a path toward Gaza with a controversial and fateful plan that amounts to smashing not a glass ceiling but the hopes of millions of Palestinians and sculpting the future of the region in a manner that not even its harshest critics could have predicted would be decided under U.S. auspices.
title: Trump’s backing for Israel's Gaza strategy dashes last hopes for peace

description: French President Emmanuel Macron will host Syrian counterpart Ahmed al-Sharaa on Wednesday for the former terrorist leader’s first European visit, the French presidency told AFP.
title: Macron to host Syria's al-Sharaa

description: Friedrich Merz will be the German chancellor after winning a vote in the Bundestag Tuesday afternoon, following an embarrassing initial failure that plunged Berlin into political turmoil, Politico reported.
title: Merz becomes German chancellor in second Bundestag vote

description: The EU on Tuesday unveiled a long-promised plan to phase out its remaining gas imports from Russia by the end of 2027, a challenge given Europe's continued dependence on Russian fossil fuels.
title: EU unveils long-promised plan to quit Russian gas by end-2027

description: Israel’s far-right Finance Minister Bezalel Smotrich has asserted that Israel will be in a position to “declare victory” in Gaza “within months”, according to Arutz Sheva.
title: Smotrich says Gaza’s population to be expelled abroad ‘within months’

description: TEHRAN-A Persian translation of Canadian novelist Margaret Atwood’s novel “Lady Oracle” has recently been published by Qoqnus Publications in Tehran.
title: “Lady Oracle” appears in Iranian bookstores

description: TEHRAN- Prominent Iranian composer and guitarist Soheil Nafisi is set to perform a selection of his works at Rudaki Hall on Wednesday.
title: Guitarist Soheil Nafisi to perform at Tehran’s Rudaki Hall

description: TEHRAN- An adaptation of American playwright Arthur Miller’s 1970 play “The Archbishop's Ceiling” is on stage at the Neauphle-le-Chateau Theater in Tehran.
title: “The Archbishop's Ceiling” on stage at Tehran theater

description: TEHRAN-The 1952 Japanese tragedy film “Ikiru” (“To Live”) directed by Akira Kurosawa will be shown at the Iranian Artists Forum (IAF) in Tehran on Thursday.
title: IAF to screen Kurosawa’s “Ikiru”

description: TEHRAN-This year, more publishers from the general category have applied to attend the 36th Tehran International Book Fair (TIBF) fair compared to last year, Ebrahim Heidari, the spokesperson and deputy director of the fair, said at a press conference on Monday at the Ministry of Culture and Islamic Guidance in Tehran.
title: 2,363 domestic publishers to attend 36th Tehran International Book Fair

description: Canada’s Prime Minister, Mark Carney, met with the U.S. president, Donald Trump, on Tuesday in a closely watched encounter at the White House that could hint at the future relationship between the two countries and their two leaders.
title: Trump and Canada’s Carney meet at White House

description: TEHRAN - A high-ranking delegation from Mongolia visited the National Museum of Iran on Monday to explore opportunities for expanded cultural and museum cooperation between the two nations.
title: Mongolian delegation visits Iran’s National Museum, explores avenues for expanded cultural ties

description: TEHRAN  – A festival of Iranian tribes, alongside a handicrafts and souvenirs exhibition, officially opened on Monday evening in the scenic Besh Qardash area of Bojnurd, the capital of North Khorasan province in northeastern Iran.
title: Festival of Iranian tribes kicks off in Bojnurd

description: TEHRAN – A senior Iranian tourism official has said that the spread of negative media narratives about Iran – commonly referred to as Iranophobia – poses a significant challenge to the country’s tourism sector, even as visa requirements for most travelers have been eased or eliminated.
title: Iran eases visas, but media misinformation still a barrier to tourism

description: TEHRAN - Iran’s Interests Section in Washington, D.C. has announced a reduction in the validity period for tourist and entry visas issued to U.S. applicants.
title: Iran announces adjustment to visa validity for U.S. applicants

description: TEHRAN – On Tuesday, Iran’s Minister of Cultural Heritage, Tourism, and Handicrafts, Seyyed Reza Salehi-Amiri, called for a transformative approach to tourism as a driver of sustainable peace and Islamic civilizational renewal during the 5th D-8 Senior Officials Meeting on Tourism, held Tuesday in Cairo.
title: Iran proposes strategic tourism roadmap at D-8 meeting in Cairo

description: TEHRAN – Iranian Transport and Urban Development Minister Farzaneh Sadeq and Qatari Prime Minister and Minister of Foreign Affairs Sheikh Mohammed bin Abdulrahman bin Jassim Al Thani met in Doha on Tuesday, aiming to boost bilateral relations in the transport sector.
title: Iran, Qatar discuss ways to enhance transport ties

description: TEHRAN – According to the United Nations Development Program’s (UNDP) latest Human Development Report (HDR) 2025, Iran has been placed among the countries with a High Development Index (HDI).
title: Iran among UNDP’s High Human Development countries

description: TEHRAN – The preparation of a document for the development of nanotechnology in Venezuela using Iran’s knowledge and expertise has been discussed by officials from the two countries.
title: Venezuela to utilize Iran’s expertise in nanotechnology

description: TEHRAN – A total of 979,923 births were registered in the country in the past Iranian calendar year (March 2024 – March 2025), the Civil Registration Organization has announced.
title: Some 980,000 births registered in a year

description: TEHRAN – Brigadier General Hossein Zolfaqari, the Secretary General of Iranian Drug Control Headquarters (DCHQ), and Monika Oledzka Nielson, the United Nation Children’s Fund (UNICEF) ad interim Representative in Iran, have underscored the need for the development of a cooperative model between the two organizations to be able to realize joint objectives and enhance the efficiency of collaborative measures.
title: DCHQ, UNICEF highlight developing partnership model

description: TEHRAN-The 6th edition of the 5 Film & Photo Awards has announced the members of the jury for the film section.
title: Renowned Iranian, international figures to serve in film jury of 5 Film & Photo Awards

description: BEIJING- The 46th anniversary celebration of The Tehran Times, attended by Chinese Ambassador Cong Peiwu, underscored the vital role of media in strengthening the relations between Iran and China.
title: Ink and influence: Tehran Times at the heart of Iran-China friendship

description: TEHRAN – Iran has ramped up its gasoline production to 120 million liters per day in the second Iranian calendar month of Ordibehesht (started on April 21), up from 107 million liters the previous month, even as the country’s refining industry reports a dramatic collapse in profitability, a senior industry official said on Tuesday.
title: Daily gasoline output hits 120m liters

description: BEIJING- In an era dominated by Western media narratives—where misinformation can often be spun as fact—promoting independent voices from the Global South has never been more crucial.
title: From fact-checking to fairness: How Chinese media challenges Western narratives

description: TEHRAN – Iran has increased its thermal power generation capacity by 10 percent compared to last year, as the country braces for record-breaking electricity demand this summer, a senior energy official said.
title: Thermal power generation rises 10% ahead of peak summer demand

description: TEHRAN – The 2025 edition of Iran’s Expo has drawn strong interest from international visitors and created new opportunities for long-term business partnerships, according to a senior official from the Iran Chamber of Commerce, Industries, Mines and Agriculture (ICCIMA).
title: ‘Expo 2025 spurs interest in Iran’s investment potential’

description: TEHRAN – Iran's economy grew by 2.8 percent in the Iranian calendar year 1403 (ended March 20, 2025), with non-oil growth reaching 2.7 percent, according to the latest report by the Iranian Parliament (Majlis) Research Center.
title: Majlis Research Center reports 2.8% GDP growth for Iran in 2024–25

description:
TEHRAN- The chairman of Iran-Iraq Joint Chamber of Commerce said that the value of Iran's annual non-oil export to Iraq can be increased to $20 billion.
Iran and Iraq have a strategic relationship that can grow and develop with an economic focus, Yahya Al-e Eshaq noted.
title: Iran's non-oil export to Iraq can rise to $20b

description: A senior Hamas official said on Tuesday the group was no longer interested in truce talks with Israel and urged the international community to halt Israel's "hunger war" against Gaza.
title: No point in further Gaza truce talks, Hamas says

description: TEHRAN – Shahrdari Gorgan defeated Tabiat 98-95 on Monday to win the 2024/25 Iranian Basketball Super League (IBSL) championship.
title: Shahrdari Gorgan clinch 2024/25 Iran Basketball League title

description: TEHRAN - Iran had a 1-2 finish in both the heaviest men’s events on the final day of the 2025 World Youth and Junior Championships in Lima, Peru. The women’s winners on an all-juniors program were from Turkmenistan and Turkey.
title: 2025 World Youth and Junior Championships: Iran’s big four dominate heavyweights

description: TEHRAN - Iran concluded their FIFA Beach Soccer World Cup Seychelles 2025 Group B campaign with a 7-5 defeat to two-time champions Portugal on Monday.
title: Iran lose to Portugal in 2025 Beach Soccer World Cup

description: TEHRAN – The Tehran Times, Iran’s oldest English-language newspaper, celebrated its 46th anniversary on Monday afternoon in a ceremony attended by foreign ambassadors, media executives, and senior cultural officials in Tehran.
title: Chinese ambassador calls for stronger media ties between Iran and China
